# No Verbose Comments

Prefer clear code over long comments. Comments should add value, not restate what the code does.

## Do

- Omit comments when the code is self-explanatory (names, structure).
- Use brief comments only for non-obvious intent, invariants, or "why" not "what".
- Prefer better names and small functions over comment blocks.

## Don't

- Don't write paragraph-style or step-by-step comments that repeat the code.
- Don't add section headers or decorative comments (e.g. "// 1. Update workout").
- Don't comment every line or every block; trust readable code.

## Examples

```go
// ❌ Verbose
// Build sets of incoming IDs (only non-zero IDs are "existing" items being updated)
incomingExerciseIDs := utils.NewSet[uint](0)

// ✅ Omit when obvious, or one short line only when it helps
incomingExerciseIDs := utils.NewSet[uint](0)
```

```typescript
// ❌ Verbose
// Validate and prepare exercises for the API payload
const exercises = values.exercises.map(...)

// ✅ Omit; the variable name and structure are clear
const exercises = values.exercises.map(...)
```

When in doubt: if removing the comment doesn't lose real information, remove it.
